{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review — [T3] Integration feasibility (overlay): NOT-APPLICABLE / PASS.\n\nThis overlay applies only when a plan integrates an external API/CLI/service/library or asserts a previously-unused capability. This story does neither — it builds an INTERNAL, provider-agnostic primitive on already-shipped machinery:\n\n- Reducer fold + compaction-survival: process_create / process_link / process_snapshot and SNAPSHOT/compact already exist (src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:19, 203, 515, 648; replay_events SNAPSHOT handling at 647).\n- The outbound intent-gate pattern it generalizes (local_label_intent) is already shipped (src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py:1104,1365–1371; reconcile.py:602,894,931).\n- The new should_propagate_removal(ref, managed_refs) is an internal helper, not an external endpoint/subcommand.\n\nExternal systems are referenced only as out-of-scope context, not as dependencies of THIS story: Jira is the existing, already-used integration (apply_inbound.py / shipped reconciler); Linear/GitHub are \"planned\" and explicitly OUT OF SCOPE (\"actual Linear/GitHub providers\"); Unito/Exalate/FolderSync/Syncthing/ghas-jira-integration appear as prior-art validation only. The gate is explicitly \"provider-agnostic (no Jira-specific logic)\" and verified via unit tests, not cross-system call-sites. Per the T3 ANTI-FP clause, an internal/already-used integration is not-applicable.\n\nChecklist disposition:\n- Achievable as described / capability gap — PASS (no external capability asserted; gap n/a).\n- Named subcommands/endpoints exist (MATCH/MISMATCH/UNVERIFIED) — n/a (no external endpoints are dependencies of this story).\n- Auth/HTTPS preconditions — n/a (no external transport introduced here).\n- Critical gap routes to a SPIKE — n/a (no gap).\n\nAffirmations: criteria T3(a)(b)(c)(d) all satisfied as not-applicable. No T3 findings."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782538324925845001,"uuid":"47154be9-f1fb-4241-a359-c3aa0000c230"}